review_1.column_1_text:

DISREGARD means ‘ignore or pay no attention to something’.

success.question_text: TRIPLET is to THREE as QUINTUPLET is to
success.question_category_path: General Ability / Verbal Reasoning / Analogies

review_1.column_1_text:
Explanation

TRIPLETS are THREE offspring born at the same time to the same mother. QUINTUPLETS are FIVE offspring born at the same time to the same mother.

success.question_text:
These words run in pairs. Insert the missing word to complete the third pair.

      DELIGHT—DELIGHTFUL
      HARM—HARMFUL
      GLORY—___________
success.question_category_path: General Ability / Verbal Reasoning / Word Skills

review_1.column_1_text:
Explanation

DELIGHT, HARM and GLORY are nouns. The adjectives formed from these nouns are DELIGHTFUL, HARMFUL and GLORIOUS.

success.question_text: Add one letter to the word ONCE. Rearrange the letters to make a word meaning a small bread-like bun often served with butter and jam. The added letter is
success.question_category_path: General Ability / Verbal Reasoning / Anagrams

review_1.column_1_text:
Explanation

The letter added to ONCE is S. The rearranged letters form the word SCONE.

success.question_category_path: General Ability / Non-Verbal Reasoning / Reasoning

review_1.column_1_text: Solution

review_3.column_1_text:
The third column contains the common parts of both column 1 and column 2 in each row.

Tip

The matrix consists of nine squares containing shapes which form a pattern. Look along a row, or down a column, to see how each tile is related to the next and use this relationship to find the shapes in the missing tile.

success.question_text: The word FORCEFUL is most nearly the opposite in meaning to
success.question_category_path: General Ability / Verbal Reasoning / Opposites and Similars

review_1.column_1_text:
Explanation

FORCEFUL means ‘powerful, full of force’. WEAK has the opposite meaning: ‘not strong’.

success.question_text:
Which two of the following statements together prove that:

SOME DOGS ARE ALLOWED IN RESTAURANTS.

I. Guide dogs are allowed to stay with their owners.

II. Pet dogs are not allowed in restaurants.

III. Rules for dogs do not always apply to guide dogs.

IV. Guide dog owners can be served in restaurants.
success.question_category_path: General Ability / Verbal Reasoning / Logic

review_1.column_1_text:
Explanation

(I and IV) Guide dogs are allowed to stay with their owners. Guide dog owners can be served in restaurants.

DILUTE, WATER DOWN and ADULTERATE refer to making something less pure. LIQUEFY means ‘cause something to become liquid’.

success.question_text: Which is the odd one out?
success.question_category_path: General Ability / Non-Verbal Reasoning / Reasoning

review_1.column_1_text: Solution

review_3.column_1_text:
Each shape is a triangle with small circles and lines. Three of the triangles have the black circle at one vertex and the white circle at the next vertex in a clockwise direction. The 4th triangle has the white circle at the next vertex in an anticlockwise direction.

Tip

See how one of the objects is different from the other three.

success.question_text: Which word is the odd one out?
success.question_category_path: General Ability / Verbal Reasoning / Odd One Out

review_1.column_1_text:
Explanation

IMPEDE, HINDER and THWART all carry a sense of preventing something from happening or someone being successful. DEVIATE means ‘turn aside from a particular course of action’.

success.question_text: FLEDGLING is to BIRD as _________ is to FISH.
success.question_category_path: General Ability / Verbal Reasoning / Analogies

review_1.column_1_text:
Explanation

A FLEDGLING is a young BIRD. A FINGERLING is a young FISH.

success.question_text: The word IDLY is most nearly the opposite in meaning to

review_1.column_1_text:
Explanation

An IDLE person is lazy or lacking energy. A person who works ENERGETICALLY is hardworking and industrious.

success.question_text:

for     pay     me     it     is     rise     time     to     for     a     apply
